Back then we only had cases in the low hundreds. and despite making it illegal not to wear masks, having almost everything that wasn't a food shop or a chemist close down, telling everyone to stay indoors as much as possible etc... it still spread from that small number to a hundred thousand. Italy waited a long time to take action and now they are in a bad way. Borris Johnson has basically said he wants to wait until summer to do anything because he doesn't want to add too much strain to the NHS. The UK has about a hundred cases and they are still giving people a choice on how they want to react and not closing the schools, non essential buildings etc. From what I've experienced the action they eventually take will last a much longer time the longer they wait to act. If they act now they could be rid of this thing quite quickly. In a month they could have 1000 times more cases.
